%global packname  chemCal
%global packver   0.2.1
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.2.1
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Calibration Functions for Analytical Chemistry

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Simple functions for plotting linear calibration functions and estimating
standard errors for measurements according to the Handbook of Chemometrics
and Qualimetrics: Part A by Massart et al. There are also functions
estimating the limit of detection (LOD) and limit of quantification (LOQ).
The functions work on model objects from - optionally weighted - linear
regression (lm) or robust linear regression ('rlm' from the 'MASS'
package).

